        "title": "Tesh Khullar Joins Flatiron Health as VP of Provider Solutions",
        "slug": "tesh",
        "body": "Hire set to expand Flatironâs network and enhance solutions offering to provider partners\n**NEW YORK, NY, July 8, 2014** &nbsp;â Flatiron Health is announcing the appointment of Tesh Khullar as its VP of Provider Solutions. Tesh brings over 14 years of experience working in community oncology in a variety of roles, including IT, distribution, business development, and sales. Teshâs experience will be instrumental in leading Flatiron Health through the next phase of its growth, and accelerating its mission to improve cancer care.  \n  \n Flatiron Health aims to improve cancer care by organizing the worldâs real-world oncology data and making it useful for patients, physicians and researchers. Teshâs expertise in community oncology will help Flatiron Health strengthen its relationships with provider partners, while ensuring that Flatiron Health delivers value to oncologists and practice administrators through its OncologyCloud<sup>TM</sup> platform. OncologyCloud<sup>TM</sup> consists of the following applications: OncoEMR<sup>TM</sup>, the leading cloud-based oncology-specific EMR platform; OncoAnalytics<sup>TM</sup>, a real-time business and clinical intelligence application for cancer centers; and SeeYourChart<sup>TM</sup>, a patient portal.  \n  \n âI couldnât be more excited to join Flatiron Health and help providers improve the continuum of care with technology,â said Tesh Khullar, vice president of provider solutions. âFlatiron has the technical capabilities to build a data foundation that will truly enhance the quality of care and patient experience.â   \n  \n âTesh joining Flatiron will allow us to accelerate our mission of providing value to oncologists through data and technology,â said Nat Turner, Flatiron Healthâs co-founder and CEO. âHis relationships and knowledge in oncology will be an asset to Flatiron and our provider partners.â   \n  \n\nAbout Tesh Khullar\n Tesh Khullar has 14 years of experience in community oncology, in a variety of roles including IT, distribution, business development, and sales. Tesh joins Flatiron Health from McKesson Corporation, where he served most recently as the National VP of Oncology Sales and Account Management. In this capacity, Tesh was responsible for $4B in sales and led a team of 40 account executives, business development executives, and specialists focused on delivering value to the independent oncology practices across the nation. Passionate about the oncology space and making the process of navigating the cancer care continuum more efficient, Tesh will utilize his 14+ years of experience in the cancer care community at Oncology Therapeutics Network and McKesson Specialty Health to help Flatiron create patient-focused solutions for its provider partners.  \n  \n\nAbout Flatiron Health, Inc.\n Flatiron Health is a health care technology company and operator of the OncologyCloudâ¢ platform. By integrating across the entire clinical data spectrum, Flatiron Health allows cancer care providers and life science companies to gain deep business and clinical intelligence through its web-based platform. The company was started by Nat Turner and Zach Weinberg, two of the founders of Invite Media, and is backed by Google Ventures, First Round Capital, LabCorp, and other venture capital groups and angel investors. For more information, please visit [www.flatiron.com](http://www.flatiron.com).   \n  \n\nPress Contact   \n\n Flatiron Health, Inc.  \n [press@flatiron.com](mailto:press@flatiron.com)",
        "publishAt": "2015-07-20"
      }
